> Any differences between those two?

If use  std::mutex in a bthread context, then the bthread will hang up and the bthread's underlying pthread will also hang up. But there are a limit number of pthread  workers for bthread (the default cpu core num). If all pthreads are hang up then brpc could not work correctly. Sometimes we will get failed to connect error or rpc timeout error.
